The corrected `add` function resizes `num` to the maximum size needed before starting the loop, ensuring no out-of-bounds accesses occur. The loop then continues up to `maxsize` or until there are no more carries to add, ensuring that all digits and carries are accurately accounted for. If there's a carry after processing the most significant digit, it's pushed back to the `num` vector, expanding it accordingly.
